article.headline: Fields powers Georgia Southern to 41-17 victory
article.description: Wesley Fields ran for 148 yards and two third-quarter touchdowns to help Georgia Southern pull away for a 41-17 victory over Coastal Carolina on Saturday.
article.linkText: Fields powers Georgia Southern to 41-17 victory

images.name: Georgia Southern RB takes off for long TD
images.caption: Georgia Southern running back Logan Wright bursts through the hole and out runs the defense for a 59-yard touchdown run.

video.headline: Georgia Southern RB takes off for long TD
video.caption: Georgia Southern running back Logan Wright bursts through the hole and out runs the defense for a 59-yard touchdown run.
video.title: Georgia Southern RB takes off for long TD
video.description: Georgia Southern running back Logan Wright bursts through the hole and out runs the defense for a 59-yard touchdown run.

article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- Wesley Fields ran for 148 yards and two third-quarter touchdowns to help Georgia Southern pull away for a 41-17 victory over Coastal Carolina on Saturday. The Eagles (8-3, 5-2 Sun Belt Conference) trailed 10-3 early in the second quarter before ripping off 38 unanswered points. Shai Werts' 12-yard TD run pulled Georgia Southern even at 10 with 6:35 left before halftime. The Eagles took a 13-10 lead at intermission on Tyler Bass' 20-yard field. Bass had a 44-yard field goal in the first quarter, making him a perfect 6-for-6 on attempts between 40 and 49 yards this season. Fields took over in the third quarter, scoring on runs of 6 and 2 yards, and when Logan Wright raced 59 yards for a score with 37 seconds left in the quarter the Eagles had a 34-10 lead. Monteo Garrett capped the scoring for Georgia Southern with a 5-yard fourth-quarter run. The Eagles finished with 442 yards of offense, but they had just 33 through the air. The Chanticleers (5-6, 2-5), who had just 189 total yards, fell a win shy of qualifying for a bowl game.
